<node TEXT="explanation" ID="ID_884319398" CREATED="1277697954917" MODIFIED="1277697954917">
<node TEXT="When makeAdder is called, a scope object is created with one property: a, which is the argument passed to the makeAdder function. makeAdder then returns a newly created function. Normally JavaScript&apos;s garbage collector would clean up the scope object created for makeAdder at this point, but the returned function maintains a reference back to that scope object. As a result, the scope object will not be garbage collected until there are no more references to the function object that makeAdder returned." ID="ID_928178987" CREATED="1277697954917" MODIFIED="1277697954917"/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
