<node TEXT="Jeff on make double-triggering" ID="ID_1478831228" CREATED="1365195852814" MODIFIED="1365195860459">
<node ID="ID_415180252" CREATED="1365195861466" MODIFIED="1365195861466"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <div>
      It should run only once, but that seems to vary depending on which version of Make is installed. My suggestion would be to explicitly run one of the targets only, then check with -n to see if it would run that step again. If it would, you've probably got a subtle error. If it would not, then it is probably make double-counting and not checking properly when things have been computed.
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
<node ID="ID_1594015853" CREATED="1365195861468" MODIFIED="1365195861468"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <div>
      I have also noticed that some SAS procedures that should be read-only modify their inputs once in a while. Obviously, this can cause problems, too.
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
