<node TEXT="quoting Jeff S" LOCALIZED_STYLE_REF="AutomaticLayout.level,1" ID="ID_1353842502" CREATED="1351630655531" MODIFIED="1351630661909">
<node TEXT="You could even use a pattern rule like this:&#xa;&#xa;%.dta: %.sas7bdat&#xa;st $&lt; $@&#xa;&#xa;Details on writing rules like that are here:&#xa;http://www.gnu.org/software/make/manual/make.html#Pattern-Rules" ID="ID_1622693209" CREATED="1351630649219" MODIFIED="1352429221875"/>
<node TEXT="why he suggested that" LOCALIZED_STYLE_REF="AutomaticLayout.level,1" ID="ID_1307029119" CREATED="1352429223792" MODIFIED="1352429233402">
<node ID="ID_1765095751" CREATED="1352429226119" MODIFIED="1352429226119"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      You've got a sas call that runs the prevalent cohort, then two stat transfer calls that copy both prev and inc files. I'd recommend putting dta outputs as their own targets.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
