<node TEXT="story" ID="ID_624382945" CREATED="1362599564693" MODIFIED="1363026356389">
<node TEXT="The process I&apos;m using to generate disease identifiers is almost identical to the one for treatment identifiers -- ICD9-keyed lookup based on a table provided by John. Similarly to HCPCS, some files have more ICD9 codes than others, and I have yet to use the extra data in those files." ID="ID_673691826" CREATED="1362599566524" MODIFIED="1362599730337"/>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="treatment" ID="ID_870835557" CREATED="1362530824544" MODIFIED="1362530825787">
<node TEXT="treat_*" ID="ID_903253633" CREATED="1362531089713" MODIFIED="1362531091884"/>
<node TEXT="history" ID="ID_293352399" CREATED="1362599534693" MODIFIED="1362599536320">
<node TEXT="There are three boolean variables for the three treatments of interest. Each claim has a number of HCPCS codes associated with it. If any of them appear in the lookup file John provided, the field is a 1; otherwise it is a 0." ID="ID_1840134615" CREATED="1362599237733" MODIFIED="1362599327430"/>
<node TEXT="Since multiple HCPCS codes are associated with a claim, these values are not a partition -- a single claim could involve, for instance, both ONS and parenteral nutrition." ID="ID_494452033" CREATED="1362599334130" MODIFIED="1362599376750"/>
</node>
